setSystemErr

public static void setSystemErr(String testName)
Redirects system error output to the a file whose name is constructed form testName. If 'testName' is null, restores system error to the printstream that was in place before the last call with on-null testName. The intent is that this be called in pairs, first with a testName, then with null. Note: If there's a chance that an exception will be thrown in the code between a pair of calls to this method, put the first in a try block and the 2nd in a finally block. If the stream does not get reset, the next test will inherit the stream that write to a file.
